body:
@chanchanzhang as @achowdhery said, please use `object_detection/export_tflite_ssd_graph.py` rather than `optimized_for_inference.py`. And the tflite model file I used is from the one used by Android example. You can get it [here](https://storage.googleapis.com/download.tensorflow.org/models/tflite/coco_ssd_mobilenet_v1_0.75_quant_2018_06_29.zip).

@achowdhery I think there are not FakeQuant nodes and tensors in checkpoints of [ssd_mobilenet_v1_quantized_coco](http://download.tensorflow.org/models/object_detection/ssd_mobilenet_v1_quantized_300x300_coco14_sync_2018_07_03.tar.gz)  and [ssd_mobilenet_v1_0.75_depth_quantized_coco](http://download.tensorflow.org/models/object_detection/ssd_mobilenet_v1_0.75_depth_quantized_300x300_coco14_sync_2018_07_03.tar.gz). Could you check them?
